03:19.309 --> 03:21.062
_

03:21.139 --> 03:23.139
[Rustling]

03:28.713 --> 03:31.881
Ben: French toast with bacon or
scrambled eggs with hash browns?

03:35.787 --> 03:37.520
I'm really good at cooking.

03:37.555 --> 03:39.129
I'll probably be a chef someday.

03:40.391 --> 03:41.958
I had a mouse down here.

03:41.993 --> 03:43.308
Her name was Lola.

03:44.662 --> 03:46.183
What's your favorite book?

03:48.045 --> 03:50.519
Breakfast is the most important
meal of the day.

03:57.622 --> 03:58.885
What's your name?

04:03.414 --> 04:04.792
You got to eat.

04:07.285 --> 04:08.517
[Sighs]

04:08.553 --> 04:10.690
Okay, more for me.

04:12.178 --> 04:13.738
I hate eggs.

04:16.394 --> 04:17.911
French toast it is.

04:31.976 --> 04:33.409
You burnt the bacon.

04:38.750 --> 04:40.716
What happens down here?

04:42.654 --> 04:43.873
We eat.

04:44.555 --> 04:45.522
We play.

04:45.990 --> 04:47.201
We have school.

04:49.127 --> 04:51.009
Sometimes our Friend comes.

04:52.280 --> 04:53.857
What does he do?

04:56.601 --> 04:58.265
He brings toys.

05:01.739 --> 05:04.740
♪

05:06.644 --> 05:08.878
Banana pancakes or blueberry?

05:08.913 --> 05:11.681
Chocolate chip with whipped cream

05:11.716 --> 05:14.250
and hot dogs and french fries...

05:14.285 --> 05:16.552
- And root-beer floats.
- And cake.

05:16.587 --> 05:17.720
And sundaes.

05:17.755 --> 05:19.388
Tell me something new.

05:19.424 --> 05:21.590
They killed Saddam Hussein.

05:23.027 --> 05:26.962
♪ I've been working on the railroad ♪

05:26.998 --> 05:30.966
♪ All the livelong day ♪

05:31.002 --> 05:34.136
♪ I've been working on the railroad ♪

05:34.172 --> 05:37.994
Together: ♪ Just to pass the time away ♪

05:38.710 --> 05:42.478
I, Claire Warren, do solemnly
swear that I will support

05:42.513 --> 05:44.441
the Constitution of the United States

05:44.816 --> 05:46.817
and the Constitution
of the State of Maine,

05:47.151 --> 05:49.051
- and that I am not disqualified...
- Mayor?

05:49.087 --> 05:51.654
- ...from holding the office of Mayor.
- She's gonna be president, Daddy.

05:51.689 --> 05:54.690
♪

06:00.231 --> 06:02.898
Reporter: <i>Claire Warren
got a major victory today</i>

06:02.934 --> 06:05.034
<i>when the City Council voted to adopt</i>

06:05.069 --> 06:09.839
<i>a zero-tolerance policy
on unregistered sex offenders.</i>

06:09.874 --> 06:13.342
<i>Warren became a public figure
after the tragic murder</i>

06:13.377 --> 06:16.612
<i>of her young son, Adam, nine years ago.</i>

06:16.647 --> 06:19.648
♪

06:24.689 --> 06:26.055
Waffle or cinnamon roll?

06:27.925 --> 06:29.825
Tell me something new, Adam.

06:29.861 --> 06:32.561
They killed Saddam Hussein.

06:35.500 --> 06:37.500
[Scraping, rattling]

06:40.705 --> 06:43.038
- [Deep thudding]
- [Sighs]

06:45.676 --> 06:48.444
There's a steel wall.

06:48.479 --> 06:50.379
It's blocking the whole tunnel.

06:50.414 --> 06:52.414
[Breathing heavily]

06:58.779 --> 07:00.289
Prime rib for dinner?

07:00.324 --> 07:01.196
No.

07:02.360 --> 07:03.826
What about some pizza?

07:03.861 --> 07:06.195
This... that's not pizza.

07:06.230 --> 07:07.916
It's old bread.

07:13.144 --> 07:15.329
If we're good, maybe our Friend
will bring ice cream.

07:15.364 --> 07:16.577
Stop calling him that.

07:16.841 --> 07:17.909
[Scoffs] What?

07:17.944 --> 07:19.151
He's not our friend.

07:19.544 --> 07:21.076
You know what he comes here to do,

07:21.112 --> 07:22.478
and it's not bring ice cream.

07:22.958 --> 07:24.180
Adam...

07:24.215 --> 07:25.681
He's not our friend!

07:35.259 --> 07:37.226
[Leaves rustling]

07:39.246 --> 07:42.176
_

07:42.676 --> 07:45.668
Our Friend will be here soon.

07:45.703 --> 07:47.837
He'll take you to the hospital.

07:50.942 --> 07:52.575
Tell me something new.

07:55.546 --> 08:00.850
♪ I've been working on the railroad ♪

08:00.885 --> 08:06.355
♪ All the livelong day ♪

08:06.390 --> 08:11.327
♪ I've been working on the railroad ♪

08:11.362 --> 08:16.498
♪ Just to pass the time away ♪

08:17.895 --> 08:21.028
_

08:27.304 --> 08:29.204
[Door opens]

08:30.805 --> 08:32.227
Bracelet.

08:33.357 --> 08:35.076
Where is he?

08:36.260 --> 08:37.780
Bracelet.

08:40.018 --> 08:41.951
[Rattling, creaking]

08:54.865 --> 08:55.997
Key.

08:56.033 --> 08:57.145
Where is he?

08:58.401 --> 08:59.857
[Sighs] Key.

09:01.063 --> 09:03.472
[Key jingles]

09:03.507 --> 09:05.041
[Ladder rattling]

09:15.519 --> 09:17.449
[Breathes deeply]

09:18.021 --> 09:19.888
He was in a bad way.

09:22.858 --> 09:24.848
I did everything I could.

09:33.770 --> 09:35.003
[Sighs]

09:35.038 --> 09:36.721
Well, you haven't been eating.

09:37.808 --> 09:39.401
Huh?

09:40.674 --> 09:42.210
You need to eat.

09:52.756 --> 09:54.353
[Sighs]

09:55.125 --> 09:56.705
Hey, don't worry.

09:58.395 --> 10:01.263
I'll get you a new friend.

10:03.734 --> 10:06.635
♪

10:13.243 --> 10:15.644
[Door creaks, closes]

10:18.181 --> 10:19.514
Are you all right?

10:19.549 --> 10:21.082
I'm fine.

10:23.687 --> 10:25.153
You look pale.

10:28.425 --> 10:30.001
Worry about yourself.

10:31.961 --> 10:33.662
I don't think they're feeding you.

10:33.697 --> 10:35.088
You look thin.

10:36.199 --> 10:38.472
Oh. Am I clean?

10:39.002 --> 10:42.072
'Cause normally I hollow it out
and put a shank in there.

10:45.375 --> 10:46.341
Mom.

10:46.608 --> 10:47.537
Hmm?

10:49.803 --> 10:51.579
If something happens to me in here,

10:51.615 --> 10:53.730
I want you to know
that it's not your fault.

10:54.443 --> 10:55.782
What's not my fault?

10:55.817 --> 10:58.486
It's not your fault I am the way I am.

11:04.027 --> 11:05.582
You're a good boy.

11:06.330 --> 11:09.669
You always have been,
and you always will be.

11:09.933 --> 11:11.499
[Buzzer sounds in distance]

11:11.535 --> 11:13.701
Don't believe anyone who says different.

11:18.574 --> 11:19.374
Okay.

11:19.810 --> 11:21.613
Now let's do a puzzle.

11:22.713 --> 11:26.047
[Sighs]

11:26.083 --> 11:28.516
Oh, hey, I didn't know you were home.

11:28.552 --> 11:30.385
Yeah, I got a job.

11:30.420 --> 11:32.354
Oh, that's great, honey.

11:32.389 --> 11:35.510
But the dude changed his mind
and gave it to his nephew.

11:35.545 --> 11:37.278
- [Sighs]
- Nepotism, right?

11:37.691 --> 11:40.328
I'm always happy to abuse
my power on your behalf.

11:40.364 --> 11:41.463
Uh, no, no, no.

11:41.498 --> 11:42.931
Some... something will come up.

11:44.234 --> 11:46.034
Actually, um...

11:46.432 --> 11:49.804
I do have an idea for an app.

11:49.840 --> 11:51.006
Yeah?

11:51.041 --> 11:52.340
Yeah, and I know it's, like,

11:52.376 --> 11:53.875
what everybody's doing right now,

11:53.910 --> 11:55.653
but if you get the right people
together for the coding...

11:55.689 --> 11:56.745
How much?

11:57.447 --> 11:58.880
Oh, no, mom, I wasn't asking...

11:58.915 --> 11:59.703
How much do you need?

12:00.183 --> 12:04.285
Uh, like... a thousand
would probably be good.

12:04.743 --> 12:07.255
It'd be good for startup,
and I've crunched these numbers,

12:07.290 --> 12:09.206
and that's a very specific number...

12:09.733 --> 12:10.605
for a startup.

12:10.814 --> 12:12.681
What does the app do?

12:17.901 --> 12:20.001
- Going to stay for dinner?
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

12:20.037 --> 12:21.870
I just got to run
and do something real quick.

12:21.905 --> 12:24.005
And then I'll be back at dinnertime.

12:24.041 --> 12:25.358
Love you.

12:26.276 --> 12:28.209
[Door opens, closes]

12:29.780 --> 12:32.714
♪ ♪

12:45.629 --> 12:47.062
Bracelet.

12:57.874 --> 12:59.674
[Sighs]

13:02.245 --> 13:04.179
[Sighs]

13:06.349 --> 13:08.016
Hey, we talked about this.

13:08.051 --> 13:09.417
You have to eat.

13:09.453 --> 13:10.552
You're not eating.

13:10.587 --> 13:12.220
You... you're gonna be skin and bones.

13:12.255 --> 13:13.788
You can't mope around forever.

13:17.160 --> 13:19.502
I know you're sad. I'm sad, too.

13:22.766 --> 13:24.065
Where's all the bricks?

13:24.101 --> 13:25.533
Right here!

13:28.538 --> 13:30.472
[Groans]

13:30.507 --> 13:33.408
♪ ♪

13:36.146 --> 13:38.046
[Screaming]

13:48.625 --> 13:50.558
[Screaming]

14:08.078 --> 14:10.478
[Radiohead's "Where I End
and You Begin" plays]

14:22.425 --> 14:26.528
♪ There's a gap in between ♪

14:26.563 --> 14:30.298
♪ There's a gap where we meet ♪

14:30.333 --> 14:35.703
♪ Where I end and you begin ♪

14:35.739 --> 14:38.373
♪ ♪

14:38.408 --> 14:42.243
♪ I can watch and not take part ♪

14:42.279 --> 14:45.713
♪ Where I end and where you start ♪

14:45.749 --> 14:48.016
♪ Where you ♪

14:48.051 --> 14:52.187
♪ You left me alone ♪

14:52.222 --> 14:56.991
♪ You left me alone ♪

14:57.027 --> 14:58.159
[Music fades]

14:58.195 --> 15:00.094
[Sighs] Can I help you?

15:04.134 --> 15:05.233
Are you Willa?

15:05.268 --> 15:06.868
Who are you?

15:06.903 --> 15:08.079
Ben.

15:08.538 --> 15:10.338
Can I help you, Ben?

15:11.319 --> 15:13.274
It's about your brother.

15:13.310 --> 15:15.944
[Panting]

15:15.979 --> 15:17.278
[Scoffs]

15:17.314 --> 15:18.613
What did Danny do?

15:19.407 --> 15:21.282
Not Danny.

15:21.318 --> 15:22.684
Adam.

15:24.821 --> 15:25.982
Adam's...

15:27.166 --> 15:29.182
Adam died 10 years ago.

15:30.710 --> 15:32.393
He died last week.

15:36.366 --> 15:37.765
I need you to leave.

15:37.801 --> 15:39.434
No, please. I tried to help him!

15:39.469 --> 15:41.402
- I'm calling the cops.
- Wait!

15:41.438 --> 15:44.405
♪

15:50.961 --> 15:54.223
_

15:57.013 --> 15:58.947
I don't understand.

16:03.386 --> 16:05.125
He talked about you.

16:06.790 --> 16:08.684
Why did you come here?

16:09.426 --> 16:11.205
I don't have anywhere else to go.

16:11.795 --> 16:13.364
What about your family?

16:13.797 --> 16:14.843
I don't have one.

16:16.333 --> 16:17.498
I don't believe it.

16:17.534 --> 16:18.652
You don't believe what?

16:19.369 --> 16:20.501
All of it.

16:23.773 --> 16:24.839
Okay.

16:24.874 --> 16:27.775
Okay, tell me something about Adam.

16:29.746 --> 16:31.012
He played Little League.

16:31.047 --> 16:32.213
Anybody would know that.

16:32.249 --> 16:33.748
His team name was the Hornets.

16:33.783 --> 16:36.208
That... that picture
was all over the news.

16:36.620 --> 16:40.221
Your mother's name is Claire,
and your father's name is John,

16:40.257 --> 16:43.391
your brother is Danny...
- News, news, news!

16:43.426 --> 16:45.191
His favorite color is blue.

16:45.829 --> 16:48.111
His favorite Transformer is Megatron.

16:48.598 --> 16:51.933
His favorite subject is gym,
which isn't a subject.

16:51.968 --> 16:53.401
He thought that it was.

16:53.436 --> 16:54.869
We fought about that.

16:55.337 --> 16:57.529
He always woke up way too early,

16:58.208 --> 17:01.272
and he cut the tags
out of all of his shirts.

17:02.379 --> 17:04.612
And he was real sorry
when he wet the bed

17:04.647 --> 17:06.288
at that summer camp one time.

17:08.106 --> 17:09.183
But he was the most sorry

17:09.219 --> 17:11.608
when he walked away from you that day.

17:12.622 --> 17:14.559
You didn't walk away from him.

17:15.671 --> 17:17.023
He walked away from you.

17:18.160 --> 17:20.796
He always wished that he could tell you

17:20.829 --> 17:22.079
that it wasn't your fault.

17:23.733 --> 17:26.991
Because he knew that,
for the rest of your life,

17:27.369 --> 17:29.003
you would think that it was.

17:29.039 --> 17:31.973
♪ ♪

17:35.345 --> 17:37.312
[Whimpers]

17:41.451 --> 17:44.285
[Door closes]

17:44.321 --> 17:46.154
Oh.

17:46.189 --> 17:48.389
I didn't expect you till Sunday.

17:48.425 --> 17:50.658
How was Philly?

17:53.330 --> 17:55.530
I want a divorce.

17:58.835 --> 18:00.368
Do you want to throw on your tux?

18:00.403 --> 18:02.036
Um, I just had it cleaned.

18:02.072 --> 18:03.304
Did you hear me?

18:03.340 --> 18:05.306
It's another fundraiser,
but this one's really important.

18:05.342 --> 18:06.363
I'll explain on the way.

18:07.010 --> 18:09.444
I'm tired of living like this.

18:09.512 --> 18:11.579
- Just...
- I know you are, too.

18:14.751 --> 18:16.551
- We'll go to counseling.
- We've done that.

18:16.586 --> 18:19.153
No, but this time, we'll try harder.

18:19.189 --> 18:20.254
We'll fix it.

18:20.290 --> 18:22.816
There's nothing left here to fix.

18:23.593 --> 18:25.017
[Sighs]

18:25.873 --> 18:28.629
You flew home to drop this on me?

18:28.665 --> 18:29.797
Tonight?

18:29.833 --> 18:32.900
I have to give a speech
in less than an hour.

18:32.936 --> 18:34.502
It's gonna determine everything.

18:34.537 --> 18:37.004
I have worked so hard for this,

18:37.040 --> 18:38.706
and I know that you
don't care about that,

18:38.742 --> 18:41.042
but I do think
that you still care about me.

18:41.077 --> 18:44.440
So can we please... just...

18:45.593 --> 18:49.096
Can we please just do this tomorrow?

18:52.255 --> 18:53.696
You'll be great.

18:54.691 --> 18:56.000
You always are.

19:02.499 --> 19:04.732
[Shower running]

19:04.768 --> 19:07.702
♪ ♪

19:16.479 --> 19:17.812
How was your shower?

19:18.705 --> 19:20.448
It was too hot.

19:24.120 --> 19:27.433
So, there wasn't the best selection.

19:28.158 --> 19:30.224
Thank you.

19:48.077 --> 19:50.011
[Sighs]

19:52.749 --> 19:54.782
[Sighs] Let me see that hand.

19:54.818 --> 19:56.117
Oh.

20:01.391 --> 20:02.974
So, what are we gonna do?

20:04.828 --> 20:06.761
Go to the police.

20:06.796 --> 20:07.962
Okay.

20:08.624 --> 20:10.064
Tomorrow.

20:12.068 --> 20:16.929
Um, my mom has a... has a big
speech tonight, and...

20:17.474 --> 20:20.875
when she hears that Adam
was alive just a week ago...

20:20.910 --> 20:22.210
I understand.

20:26.516 --> 20:28.449
[Jazz music playing]

20:28.485 --> 20:30.418
[Indistinct conversations]

20:34.824 --> 20:36.390
How's the new pool, Jimmy?

20:36.426 --> 20:38.746
Glad we could work out
that easement issue for you.

20:39.128 --> 20:40.628
- Joanne.
- Hi.

20:40.663 --> 20:41.666
Hi.

20:43.066 --> 20:44.699
She's a star.

20:45.068 --> 20:45.996
A rising one.

20:46.302 --> 20:48.102
She'll make one heck of a governor.

20:48.137 --> 20:50.204
She'll definitely on our list
for the next cycle.

20:50.240 --> 20:52.673
Why wait? It's up to you guys.

20:52.709 --> 20:55.076
Do you want the Governor's mansion now

20:55.111 --> 20:57.111
or wait four more years?

20:57.701 --> 20:59.081
You let me know.

21:06.656 --> 21:08.422
- [Knock on door]
- [Gasps]

21:08.458 --> 21:09.774
Willa: Mom?

21:11.194 --> 21:13.238
Mom? It's almost time.

21:13.763 --> 21:15.363
[Whimpers]

21:15.398 --> 21:16.878
Is everything all right?

21:19.402 --> 21:21.602
What is it? What's wrong?

21:21.638 --> 21:22.904
[Crying]

21:22.939 --> 21:24.219
Okay, okay.

21:24.288 --> 21:25.439
I...

21:26.543 --> 21:28.175
I don't...

21:28.211 --> 21:30.144
Here.

21:30.179 --> 21:31.679
Come over here.

21:31.714 --> 21:34.248
[Gasping]

21:34.284 --> 21:36.232
Undo this.

21:37.020 --> 21:38.920
[Breathing heavily, crying]

21:38.955 --> 21:41.122
Okay.

21:41.157 --> 21:42.790
Okay.

21:42.825 --> 21:44.859
[Panting]

21:44.894 --> 21:46.193
I can't.

21:46.229 --> 21:48.195
- I can't.
- It's all right.

21:48.231 --> 21:51.766
- Oh, my God.
- Everything is going to be fine.

21:51.801 --> 21:53.200
[Panting]

21:53.236 --> 21:55.102
Everything is gonna be fine.

21:55.138 --> 21:57.104
Take some deep breaths.

21:59.475 --> 22:01.309
Thank you.

22:04.714 --> 22:06.781
[Sniffles]

22:07.211 --> 22:10.618
Claire: The Republican Party
hasn't governed

22:10.653 --> 22:14.355
the state of Maine in over a decade.

22:14.390 --> 22:18.492
We can only take back our great state

22:18.528 --> 22:23.615
by pushing one thing...
the sanctity of family.

22:24.400 --> 22:28.895
They say you can't choose your family.

22:29.505 --> 22:31.047
But you know what?

22:31.641 --> 22:36.598
I would have chosen
exactly who I was given.

22:36.878 --> 22:39.013
[Applause]

22:39.048 --> 22:41.382
Well, what...
what do you mean, he's gone?

22:41.417 --> 22:43.384
The two of you were supposed
to be watching him!

22:43.419 --> 22:45.086
Danny: He was fine.
He was with Willa, and...

22:45.121 --> 22:46.621
John: But you're the oldest!
You're in charge!

22:46.656 --> 22:48.689
Willa: Except when he's getting
to third base with some slut.

22:48.725 --> 22:50.992
Like you'd ever know what
that is, you freak of nature.

22:51.027 --> 22:52.927
- [Door opens]
- Nina: It's okay. Here he is.

22:52.962 --> 22:54.261
- [Door closes]
- Claire: Oh!

22:54.297 --> 22:55.830
Oh, thank God.

22:55.865 --> 22:56.998
Oh, my God. Thank God.

22:57.033 --> 22:58.566
Don't you run off like that ever again.

22:58.601 --> 23:00.201
- Where was he?
- At an arcade downtown.

23:00.236 --> 23:01.769
He had gotten real into NBA Jam.

23:01.804 --> 23:03.337
Oh, my God. Thank you, thank you.

23:03.373 --> 23:04.739
You folks have a good night.

23:04.774 --> 23:07.875
My family has had
some very trying times.

23:07.910 --> 23:11.145
But we love each other,
and we are strong,

23:11.180 --> 23:14.882
and every family in Maine
deserves a strong foundation!

23:18.354 --> 23:23.991
What else builds
the foundation of our values,

23:24.027 --> 23:29.597
teaches us respect,
compassion, patience?

23:29.632 --> 23:32.533
[Applause]

23:32.568 --> 23:37.738
We can rebuild this great state
one brick at a time!

23:37.774 --> 23:39.507
[Applause]

23:39.542 --> 23:41.642
Thank you.

23:41.678 --> 23:43.377
Thank you.

23:43.413 --> 23:45.413
[Applause continue]

23:51.821 --> 23:53.521
How much do you know about my brother?

23:54.174 --> 23:55.857
Everything.

23:59.488 --> 24:00.601
_

24:00.662 --> 24:03.621
- Sunday brunch.
- Pancakes... John makes them.

24:03.786 --> 24:05.319
<i>Dad</i> makes them.

24:05.354 --> 24:07.054
How does it hold
all the pictures inside?

24:07.090 --> 24:09.824
How did Danny get the scar on his eye?

24:09.859 --> 24:11.358
He ran into a wall.

24:11.394 --> 24:12.860
Is that Aunt Connie?

24:12.895 --> 24:14.526
Yeah, she lives in Seattle.

24:15.164 --> 24:16.731
And Uncle Kit?

24:16.766 --> 24:18.303
Ugh, he's gross. He'll never visit.

24:18.338 --> 24:21.147
Adam really liked his naked-lady tattoo.

24:21.637 --> 24:25.473
Um... favorite food.

24:25.508 --> 24:27.475
Spaghetti.

24:27.510 --> 24:28.584
Favorite movie?

24:28.911 --> 24:30.711
Uh, "Nacho Libre."

24:30.747 --> 24:32.046
Pet?

24:32.081 --> 24:34.548
The goldfish. I can't remember her name.

24:34.584 --> 24:36.279
Petunia. What happened to her?

24:36.919 --> 24:38.819
I flushed her down the toilet

24:38.855 --> 24:41.455
so she could swim free in the ocean.

24:41.491 --> 24:43.752
Favorite sport.

24:44.969 --> 24:46.369
Uh, baseball.

24:46.796 --> 24:48.144
Willa: Favorite team?

24:48.564 --> 24:50.297
The Red Sox.

24:50.333 --> 24:51.799
Willa: What are you doing?

24:51.834 --> 24:53.734
Brushing my teeth.

24:53.770 --> 24:54.835
It feels so good.

24:54.871 --> 24:56.604
Adam is right-handed.

24:56.639 --> 24:58.005
You have to remember that.

24:58.040 --> 25:00.207
You can't use your left hand
for anything again.

25:01.040 --> 25:02.777
This isn't gonna work.

25:02.812 --> 25:04.480
It will, it will. We just...

25:05.081 --> 25:06.914
We have to practice
and cover everything.

25:06.983 --> 25:08.624
Well, w-what if they don't believe me?

25:09.928 --> 25:10.918
They will.

25:10.953 --> 25:13.354
[Gasps]

25:20.463 --> 25:22.062
They will believe you.

25:51.627 --> 25:53.206
What are you doing?

25:54.430 --> 25:56.337
I've never seen this before.

25:57.333 --> 25:58.661
Seen what?

26:00.224 --> 26:01.576
Morning.

26:09.078 --> 26:11.011
[Sighs]

26:11.047 --> 26:12.264
You should, um...

26:13.149 --> 26:17.751
You should go to the police
tonight, before your hand heals.

26:18.056 --> 26:20.024
We got to get back to work.

26:21.991 --> 26:23.560
Why are you doing this?

26:25.361 --> 26:27.128
Because Adam was wrong.

26:30.099 --> 26:31.455
It wasn't his fault.

26:39.202 --> 26:41.400
But now I can fix...

26:42.832 --> 26:44.705
everything.

26:51.280 --> 26:52.484
[Sighs]

26:55.258 --> 26:56.661
John: Hey, where've you been?

26:57.159 --> 27:00.027
At a... cheap motel
with a dirty stranger.

27:00.062 --> 27:01.061
[Chuckles]

27:03.766 --> 27:05.211
You're leaving again?

27:05.835 --> 27:09.670
They, uh... yeah, they booked
some readings in San Francisco.

27:09.705 --> 27:11.071
Do you want to come?

27:11.444 --> 27:15.442
Or, here's a crazy idea...
you, uh, stay home.

27:23.653 --> 27:25.404
Your mom and I...

27:29.058 --> 27:30.628
You're getting a divorce.

27:34.864 --> 27:36.864
That's... that's a mistake.

27:36.899 --> 27:38.423
- No, honey...
- Y-you should stick it out

27:38.448 --> 27:39.233
a few more days.

27:39.268 --> 27:40.601
- No, it won't matter.
- It will.

27:40.636 --> 27:42.069
It... trust me. It will.

27:42.104 --> 27:44.238
No, it's been over for a long time.

27:44.273 --> 27:45.483
It was just Adam.

27:45.518 --> 27:48.175
- If that hadn't happened, you wo...
- No, we'd have broken anyway.

27:48.210 --> 27:50.887
- What?
- Mom and I are different people.

27:51.860 --> 27:55.417
All Adam did was
show us how true that was.

27:59.322 --> 28:03.223
Did you know that your little
brother hardly ever cried?

28:03.550 --> 28:05.066
I mean, he did, of course, but...

28:05.761 --> 28:08.829
He... the kid was
a little ray of sunshine.

28:08.864 --> 28:09.348
So?

28:09.373 --> 28:13.056
So he'd hate what we're
doing to ourselves now.

28:13.903 --> 28:15.936
[Sighs]

28:16.328 --> 28:17.992
We're wallowing.

28:19.544 --> 28:21.159
It's time to move on.

28:25.481 --> 28:26.783
He'd want us to.

28:27.249 --> 28:30.150
♪ ♪

29:00.944 --> 29:02.349
[Bell rings in distance]

29:02.385 --> 29:05.319
♪ ♪

29:22.004 --> 29:23.937
[Buzzer]

29:24.740 --> 29:26.707
[Indistinct conversations]

30:01.577 --> 30:03.510
[Gasping, coughing]

30:07.483 --> 30:09.416
[Crying]

30:11.887 --> 30:13.787
[Groans]

30:13.823 --> 30:15.756
[Chuckles]

30:23.232 --> 30:25.976
I made it start bleeding again
so it looks fresh.

30:26.502 --> 30:27.674
Ben...

30:31.774 --> 30:33.136
Where are we?

30:33.809 --> 30:35.238
Bus station.

30:36.011 --> 30:37.478
Why?

30:40.249 --> 30:41.815
It won't work.

30:44.086 --> 30:45.419
- Yes, it will.
- It won't.

30:45.454 --> 30:48.225
- You said it yourself.
- No... but I can do it now.

30:48.261 --> 30:49.376
I can't.

30:52.795 --> 30:54.346
I'm sorry.

30:58.200 --> 31:01.202
Thank you f-for taking care
of him, but, uh...

31:02.671 --> 31:08.041
But I need you to leave...
and... and not come back.

31:10.546 --> 31:12.041
I, um...

31:13.282 --> 31:17.050
I packed some clothes, and...

31:17.086 --> 31:19.186
and...

31:20.556 --> 31:22.689
here's $10,000.

31:25.561 --> 31:27.369
Where am I gonna go?

31:30.681 --> 31:31.962
You can go anywhere.

31:34.003 --> 31:35.482
You can be anyone.

31:37.106 --> 31:40.237
You just can't...
you just can't be my brother.

31:50.219 --> 31:52.119
[Car door closes]

31:55.925 --> 31:57.891
[Engine starts]

31:57.927 --> 32:00.928
♪ ♪

32:40.825 --> 32:44.218
_

32:45.005 --> 32:45.819
[Door closes]

32:46.093 --> 32:47.266
Claire: Coffee or tea?

32:47.808 --> 32:50.273
Which one can I put directly in a vein?

32:52.253 --> 32:54.240
Anything exciting happening today?

32:55.182 --> 32:56.515
Pretty routine.

32:56.550 --> 32:59.084
Uh, crime stats with the Council,

32:59.026 --> 33:01.570
brunch with the Junior League,
press conference.

33:01.606 --> 33:03.770
Oh, they're gonna pound me on Keller.

33:03.806 --> 33:05.223
You did fire a Deputy Mayor.

33:05.259 --> 33:08.533
For buying his mistress La Perla
on the city's dime.

33:09.062 --> 33:10.556
Spin it with family values.

33:10.970 --> 33:13.848
You don't tolerate lying,
just ask your kids.

33:14.062 --> 33:16.006
I don't tolerate lying, Frank.

33:16.041 --> 33:17.807
I don't. You can ask my kids.

33:17.843 --> 33:19.342
- Mayor Warren!
- Holy crap.

33:19.378 --> 33:20.977
Reporter: Mayor Warren,
have you spoken to police

33:21.013 --> 33:22.879
- about the reappearance of Adam?
- Mother?

33:22.915 --> 33:24.047
What?

33:24.082 --> 33:25.916
John: Life isn't
a straight shot, my friends.

33:25.951 --> 33:28.218
It's full of hills and valleys.

33:28.253 --> 33:30.754
Confront your grief, y-your fear of it.

33:30.822 --> 33:32.225
Excuse me, folks.

33:32.724 --> 33:34.291
- Can I help you?
- Oh, my God.

33:34.326 --> 33:36.760
- They found that boy.
- What boy?

33:36.795 --> 33:39.696
The one that was murdered
years ago, the Mayor's kid.

33:39.731 --> 33:41.531
Reporter: <i>Though a body was never found,</i>

33:41.567 --> 33:43.366
<i>after an extensive investigation,</i>

33:43.402 --> 33:44.715
<i>the Warren's neighbor was eventually</i>

33:44.740 --> 33:46.703
<i>convicted for Adam's murder.</i>

33:46.738 --> 33:48.271
<i>But sources say the young man</i>

33:48.307 --> 33:51.274
<i>showed up earlier today
to a downtown police precinct</i>

33:51.310 --> 33:54.544
<i>and clearly identified himself
as the youngest Warren child.</i>

33:54.580 --> 33:56.313
- How is this happening?
- I don't know.

33:56.348 --> 33:58.415
Oh, my God. I don't understand.

33:58.450 --> 33:59.516
Me neither.

33:59.551 --> 34:02.085
He confessed!
Hank Asher said that he just...

34:02.120 --> 34:03.720
- I-I know.
- Just...

34:03.755 --> 34:05.522
It's not real. It can't be real.

34:05.557 --> 34:06.577
Mom?

34:07.759 --> 34:09.192
What if it is?

34:09.228 --> 34:11.393
He's got scars, signs of abuse.

34:11.463 --> 34:14.097
- He was kept in shackles.
- How do we know it's him?

34:14.953 --> 34:16.331
It's been 10 years.

34:16.368 --> 34:17.400
He was supposed to be dead.

34:17.436 --> 34:19.803
We ran a DNA test. It's him.

34:19.838 --> 34:21.638
Claire: Is he okay? Hi, Adam.

34:23.275 --> 34:24.741
Ben: Hi, mom.

34:34.319 --> 34:35.918
Welcome home, Ad.

34:38.902 --> 34:40.422
Nina: Just so you know,
it's kind of a mob scene

34:40.458 --> 34:41.791
back at the house with the press.

34:41.827 --> 34:43.126
Might be a little overwhelming.

34:43.161 --> 34:45.829
Can you just have them arrested?
It's private property.

34:45.864 --> 34:48.098
As soon as you all get inside,
we'll set up a perimeter.

34:48.132 --> 34:49.733
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

34:52.536 --> 34:54.471
[Car doors open]

34:54.505 --> 34:58.036
Claire: I took them all down...
photos of you.

34:58.110 --> 34:59.576
It's just, I... I couldn't...

34:59.611 --> 35:01.582
Ben: This was so high before.

35:02.888 --> 35:04.928
Do you want to go and see your room?

35:05.284 --> 35:08.218
♪ ♪

35:15.027 --> 35:16.657
It's this way.

35:25.771 --> 35:27.112
What are you doing?!

35:27.439 --> 35:29.481
I missed this place.

35:30.776 --> 35:31.940
Where's the rest of my stuff?

35:31.977 --> 35:33.537
I-it's not your stuff.

35:34.079 --> 35:35.912
- Why are you upset?
- You know why...

35:35.947 --> 35:37.681
This is what you wanted.

35:38.250 --> 35:39.449
Everything's okay now.

35:39.816 --> 35:41.050
You got your brother back.

35:41.086 --> 35:42.552
You're not my brother, Ben!

35:43.329 --> 35:45.689
You need to stop calling me that.

35:47.817 --> 35:49.145
My name is Adam.

35:49.594 --> 35:52.629
♪ ♪

35:54.341 --> 35:58.300
_

35:58.441 --> 36:01.376
♪

36:18.461 --> 36:20.428
[Cash register keys clacking]

36:26.746 --> 36:28.379
Mayor Warren?

36:28.414 --> 36:30.014
No.

36:30.049 --> 36:32.917
♪ ♪

37:11.591 --> 37:14.792
See? Told you she wasn't dead.

37:14.827 --> 37:16.761
[Indistinct conversations]

37:27.974 --> 37:30.074
Woman: Honey, please don't run.

37:30.109 --> 37:32.076
[Indistinct conversations continue]

38:05.411 --> 38:06.811
Hi.

38:10.060 --> 38:11.142
Where's mom?

38:11.774 --> 38:14.789
I'm glad you didn't listen to me
at the bus station that night.

38:15.652 --> 38:16.454
What?

38:16.489 --> 38:17.853
It's been...

38:18.424 --> 38:20.661
really nice these past few weeks...

38:21.327 --> 38:22.621
having Adam back.

38:24.764 --> 38:25.973
Is everything okay?

38:27.685 --> 38:28.933
Yeah.

38:28.968 --> 38:30.434
Why wouldn't it be?

38:32.886 --> 38:34.039
Where's mom?

38:34.797 --> 38:36.982
I'll get the nurse to discharge you.

38:40.613 --> 38:42.546
[ <i> Indistinct P.A. announcement</i> ]

38:42.582 --> 38:45.483
♪ ♪

38:49.422 --> 38:51.101
Hungry, bud?

38:51.958 --> 38:53.647
You must be sick of hospital food.

39:07.974 --> 39:10.875
♪ ♪

39:26.826 --> 39:28.039
Where is he?

39:29.447 --> 39:30.527
Kitchen.

39:31.130 --> 39:34.031
♪ ♪

39:48.981 --> 39:50.932
John: Blueberry pancakes or banana?

39:51.450 --> 39:53.918
- Either's good.
- Banana.

39:53.953 --> 39:56.854
♪ ♪

40:14.974 --> 40:16.486
Hi, mom.

40:27.687 --> 40:29.420
Welcome home.

40:29.455 --> 40:32.356
♪ ♪

